930s, the manuscript was confiscated from Zaitsev by Soviet authorities when they annexed Glaicia in 1939. The author still had proofs, however, which he revised and published in Munich in 1955. George Luckyj's translation, the first in English, now offers this indispensible biography to a new audience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Cultural Heritage.2bisacsh1 aLuckyj, George, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148758446740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487584467423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487584467/original  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles